subject: !false
message:
One of the countless things that the Internet has introduced is the rampant
abuse of the exclamation point.  Before blogs, IMs, and message boards, the 
"."-to-"!"  Ratio was something like 100-to-1.  Now that we're in the   
"OMG!!!!LOL!!!!!!"-days, it's hard enough to find a single punctuation
mark, let alone a period.

Thankfully, there's still some sanity left.  Some people are so fed up with
this overuse that they refuse to use the exclamation point anywhere.  For
anything.  Even when writing code.  Sure, it may make their code look a bit
strange, but every little bit counts...

/**
